The paper discusses the use of deep learning architectures and regularization techniques for feature extraction and interpretation, which are common topics in machine learning and neural networks (cs.LG). The focus on autoencoders and their constrained weights also suggests relevance to the sub-category of neural evolution (cs.NE). The use of the MNIST dataset and normalized object data suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), while the use of the Reuters text categorization dataset suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the mention of classification accuracy suggests relevance to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
